# Clinic Management Frontend — Cursor Rules
# Paste this file as `.cursorrules` in your project root.
# Cursor reads it automatically on every prompt in this project.

## Project Overview
You are building the React frontend for a multi-tenant clinic management system.
The backend is Django REST Framework + Supabase Auth (JWT). Every request must
carry a `Authorization: Bearer <supabase_jwt>` header. All data is scoped to
`clinic_id` on the server — the frontend never needs to filter by clinic_id itself.

## Tech Stack (do not suggest alternatives)
- React 18 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- Vite
- React Router v6 (createBrowserRouter)
- TanStack Query v5 (useQuery / useMutation)
- Zustand (auth store + ui store)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Axios (single instance in src/api/client.ts)
- @supabase/supabase-js (auth only — session management)
- react-hook-form + zod (all forms)
- date-fns (date formatting)

